# Asset Conventions (v1.5 — 3D pipeline)

This project is **transitioning off the legacy 2D PNG sprite pipeline** (`<state>/frame_NNN.png` under `assets/sprites/`). For **world content and animated entities**, do **not** add new 2D sprite sheets or frame sequences. Use **3D meshes** under `assets/models/` as validated by `tools/assets_manifest.json` and `tools/validate_assets.py`.

**Exception (temporary):** HUD/UI raster assets (9-slice panels, small icons) may remain under `assets/ui/` until a dedicated UI 3D/vector pass. That is **not** permission to add new unit or terrain PNG frame sequences.

---

## Folder structure (`assets/models/`)

Use a **flat file-per-kind** layout: one model file per logical id, not per-animation subfolders. Animations live **inside** the glTF/GLB (clips on the same rig).

```
assets/
├── models/
│   ├── environment/          # Static props: terrain tiles, rocks, trees (see manifest `environment.types`)
│   │   # e.g. grass.glb, path.glb, rock.glb, tree_pine.glb
│   ├── heroes/               # Animated: one file per class
│   │   # e.g. warrior.glb, ranger.glb, rogue.glb, wizard.glb
│   ├── enemies/              # Animated: one file per enemy type
│   ├── buildings/            # Static or animated per building type (often static .obj/.glb)
│   └── workers/              # Animated: e.g. peasant.glb, tax_collector.glb
├── audio/
│   ├── sfx/
│   └── ambient/
├── ui/                       # UI skins / icons (2D allowed here only; see note above)
└── ATTRIBUTION.md            # Required for every shipped asset file
```

Authoritative lists of **which** `kind` names exist per category are in **`tools/assets_manifest.json`** (must stay aligned with `config.py` building keys and entity types).

---

## File format rules

| Content | Allowed formats | Notes |
|--------|-----------------|--------|
| **Animated entities** (heroes, workers, enemies) | **`.glb` or `.gltf`** | Must include **embedded rigging** and animation clips. Prefer **`.glb`** for single-file deployment. |
| **Static environment** (ground, rocks, trees) | **`.obj` or `.glb` / `.gltf`** | No rig required; optimize for low-poly, flat-shaded look. |
| **Static buildings** (non-animated meshes) | **`.obj` or `.glb` / `.gltf`** | Match building type keys to simulation data; no footprint change without gameplay sign-off. |

**Forbidden for v1.5 world/entity art:** PNG/JPEG **sprite strips**, per-state folders, and `frame_000.png`-style sequences for units, buildings, or terrain.

---

## Naming rules

- **Lowercase** with **underscores** for spaces: `warrior_guild`, `skeleton_archer`, `tree_pine`.
- **Model basename** matches the manifest key: `heroes/warrior.glb`, not nested `warrior/idle/...`.
- **Building types** match `config.py` `BUILDING_COSTS` keys exactly.
- **Only** use extensions: **`.glb`**, **`.gltf`**, **`.obj`** (plus sidecars like `.mtl` only when required by a chosen `.obj`).

---

## Scale and look (replaces legacy “32×32 sprite” rules)

- Target a **low-poly, flat-shaded** look (Ursina basic lighting; avoid heavy PBR stacks unless explicitly approved).
- **One standard engine grid unit ≈ one logical mesh unit** in authored assets unless Tech/Gameplay specifies otherwise—keep scales consistent so grid placement and renderer loading stay aligned.
- **No** nearest-neighbor rules for textures on 3D meshes in the sense of pixel sprites; use **readable** UVs and materials that stay clean at runtime resolution.

---

## Licensing (non-negotiable)

- All assets must be **CC0 or permissive** (compatible with commercial Steam release).
- Every new asset file must have a corresponding entry in **`assets/ATTRIBUTION.md`**.
- Source packs belong under **`.cursor/human_provided/`** with their original license files.
- After adding assets, run: `python tools/validate_assets.py --check-attribution` (and **`--report`** as required by the current sprint).

---

## Legacy behavior (until fully removed)

- Older code paths may still generate **procedural 2D placeholders** when a model is missing; that is a **fallback**, not a target art style.
- Prefer fixing missing entries in `assets/models/` and the manifest over drawing new 2D stand-ins.

---

## Workspace hygiene (human + art)

- Remove incompatible source formats from curated import folders (e.g. `.blend`, `.fbx`, `.dae`, `.stl`) per the **v1.5 master plan**; ship only **`.glb` / `.gltf` / `.obj`** for game runtime paths.
